{
  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum number of set bits in the product of 2023 and n. This is equivalent to finding the minimum Hamming weight of a multiple of 2023. Since 2023 is not a power of 2, we need to analyze its prime factorization and use properties of binary representations or modular arithmetic to find the smallest possible weight.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "factorization_and_modular_analysis",
      "instructions": "Factorize the number 2023. Determine if 2023 is coprime to 2. Analyze the properties of the number 2023 in relation to powers of 2, specifically looking for the smallest m such that 2^m is congruent to 1 or -1 modulo 2023, or more generally, finding the smallest weight of a multiple of 2023 by checking small weights k = 1, 2, 3..."
    },
    {
      "label": "weight_search_optimization",
      "instructions": "Test if there exists an n such that k(n) = 1. This occurs if 2023*n = 2^p for some p. Test if there exists an n such that k(n) = 2. This occurs if 2023*n = 2^a + 2^b for some a, b. Test if there exists an n such that k(n) = 3. This occurs if 2023*n = 2^a + 2^b + 2^c. Use modular arithmetic (mod 2023) to check if these forms are possible for any integers a, b, c."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the factorization and modular properties from the first helper to understand the constraints on n. It will then use the results from the second helper (which systematically checks if weight 1, 2, or 3 is possible via modular congruence) to identify the smallest k(n) that satisfies the condition."
}

